The All Progressives Congress (APC) has said its primary election for Anambra governorship election will hold on June 26. Prof. Al-Mustapha Medaner, the partyâ€™s Director of Organisation, who made this known in a statement, said that the party would start the sales of expression of interest and nomination forms for the election from April 15 to June 8. According to him, the last day for submission of completed forms and accompanying documents by aspirants would be June 8. He noted that screening of aspirants would be on June 10, adding that the publication of claims and objections would be on June 12 while screening appeals would be on June 15. Medaner further explained that the governorship expression of interest form would cost N2.5 million while the nomination form would cost N20 million totalling N22.5 million. He added that physically challenged aspirants and females would only pay 50 per cent of the prescribed fees for the position.